{"id":"323565574_Rendimiento_academico_en_educacion_superior_y_su_asociacion_con_la_participacion_activa_en_la_plataforma_Moodle","abstract":"This study analyzes the association between quantity and type of access to the Moodle platform in a subject and the academic results of all students (N = 229) enrolled in their first year of psychology studies. Analysis of variance, Pearson’s correlations and multiple regression analysis were used. The results show that the use of active teaching-learning strategies is associated with better academic results. These findings underscore the importance of active student involvement, as opposed to merely accessing available information.","authors":["Cristina Jenaro","Raimundo Castaño-Calle","Elena Martín-Pastor","Noelia Flores"],"meta":["March 2018Estudios Sobre Educacion 34:177-198","DOI:10.15581/004.34.177-198","Project: Calidad docente"],"references":["323211655_Validation_of_an_Evaluation_Tutoring_Task_Scale_at_the_University","321740661_Competencias_para_la_tutoria_Experiencia_de_formacion_con_profesores_universitarios","312321932_Factores_que_Influyen_en_el_Aprendizaje_del_Idioma_Ingles_de_Nivel_Inicial_en_una_Universidad_Chilena","312136267_The_effect_of_using_online_discussion_forums_on_students'_learning","310545755_An_Investigation_of_the_Efficacy_of_Asynchronous_Discussion_on_Students'_Performance_in_an_Online_Research_Method_Course","309120076_Learning_and_teaching_styles_in_engineering_education_Engr","305342405_Empleo_de_los_Informes_de_Moodle_20_para_determinar_la_carga_y_actividad_de_estudiantes_y_profesor_Algunas_evidencias","299500673_Autoevaluacion_de_Conocimientos_Previos_y_Rendimiento_segun_Estilos_de_Aprendizaje_en_un_Grado_Universitario_de_Edificacion","299500585_Modelo_de_Calidad_de_E-learning_para_Instituciones_de_Educacion_Superior_en_Colombia","345715936_Necesidades_formativas_del_docente_universitario"]}